{
  "title": "_weakrefset Standard Library Module in Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This explainer provides a comprehensive overview of the _weakrefset standard library module introduced in Python 3.12, its purpose, key features, and examples.",

  "key_points": [
    "_weakrefset is a new module added to the Python Standard Library in version 3.12",
    "_weakrefset provides a way to create weak references to sets, which can be useful for garbage collection optimization",
    "_weakrefset maintains the order of elements in the original set and supports various set operations such as union, intersection, difference, symmetric_difference, issubset, issuperset, and membership testing",
    "_weakrefset allows you to specify a finalizer function that will be called when the referenced object is about to be garbage collected",
    "_weakrefset provides more efficient memory management compared to traditional weak references because it does not need to perform garbage collection cycles"
  ],

  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "import _weakrefset\n\nmy_set = set([1, 2, 3])\n\nweak_set = _weakrefset.refset(my_set)\n\n# Adding an element to the original set\nmy_set.add(4)\n\n# Verifying that weak_set does not contain the newly added element\nprint(_weakrefset.proxy(weak_set) != 4)"
    },
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "import _weakrefset\n\nmy_set = set([1, 2, 3])\n\nweak_set = _weakrefset.refset(my_set, finalizer=lambda obj: print(\"Finalizing {}!\".format(obj)))\n\n# Triggering the finalizer by removing my_set from its parent object\nmy_object = {'set': my_set}\ndel my_object['set']"
    }
  ],

  "version_notes": [
    "_weakrefset was introduced in Python 3.12",
    "_The finalizer function is called only when the referenced object becomes unreachable, i.e., when it's about to be garbage collected"
  ],

  "caveats": [
    "_weakrefset does not support iterating over the weak set directly. Instead, you can convert it back to a strong reference using _weakrefset.proxy()",
    "_The finalizer function will only be called once per object, even if multiple weak references point to the same object"
  ]
}
